HEADWORD: Melado
<hw>Me*la"do</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., prop. p. p. of
<ets>melar</ets> to sugar, candy, fr. L. <ets>mel</ets> honey. See
<er>Molasses</er>.]</ety> <def>A mixture of sugar and molasses; crude
sugar as it comes from the pans without being drained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

